import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.plot(data['Date'], data['CO2'])
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('CO2 Concentration')
    plt.title('What is the trend of CO2 concentration over time?')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['CO2'], bins=20)
    plt.xlabel('CO2 Concentration')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of CO2 concentration?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    data['Date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Date'], errors='ignore')
    data = data.groupby(data['Date'].dt.year).mean().reset_index()
    
    plt.bar(data['Date'], data['CO2'])
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title("What is the average CO2 concentration over the years?", wrap=True)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
